    • Method Detail

      • parse

        public DataParser<AirportEntry> parse()
        Parses CSVFile and should be first method to get called. using the Apache csv parser and Apache CSV format classes using the default charset and default format of CSV uses the InputStream made by the AbstractDataParser and is accessed using the .getSource() method as it's private and uses the .addPojo(T pojo) to add the pojo object made from each record and it uses the entries List made by AbstractDataParser and it's of type AirportEntry as you extended the AbstractCSV with AirportEntry type parameter also that's why addPojo accepts AirPortEntry
        Returns:
        Same AirportParser object used for API Flexibility to use Aggregate Operations, null if an un-handled exception happens
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if a null element was parsed
